<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/964: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from">Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-27T14:00:00+09:00">October 27, 1933—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 27—3:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>168. A press ban has been issued here forbidding comment on the “current
                            negotiations between the government of “Manchukuo” and the
                            administration of North China.”</p>
                        <p>The Embassy has no further information concerning the matter.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>